---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Research - Yonatan N. Degefu">
  <div class="research-container">
    <h1>Research</h1>

    <section class="research-overview">
      <p class="intro">
        My research combines computational modeling, systems biology, and quantitative pharmacology to understand
        and combat cancer and infectious diseases. I develop mechanistic models that bridge molecular mechanisms
        with therapeutic outcomes, enabling more rational drug combination design and revealing fundamental
        principles of cellular plasticity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="research-areas">
      <h2>Research Areas</h2>

      <div class="area">
        <h3>Melanoma Cellular Plasticity</h3>
        <p>
          Developing ODE-based mechanistic models to understand how AP-1 transcription factor networks regulate
          cell state transitions in melanoma. Using single-cell multiplexed imaging data, I build computational
          frameworks that reveal competitive and configurable interactions driving tumor heterogeneity and drug
          resistance.
        </p>
        <div class="keywords">
          <span class="keyword">Mechanistic Modeling</span>
          <span class="keyword">Transcription Factors</span>
          <span class="keyword">Cell Plasticity</span>
          <span class="keyword">Single-Cell Analysis</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="area">
        <h3>Quantitative Systems Pharmacology</h3>
        <p>
          Designing QSP models to mechanistically describe drug interactions and predict optimal combination
          therapies. My work at AstraZeneca focused on DNA damage response pathways, while previous work
          addressed tuberculosis drug combinations using high-throughput screening and machine learning.
        </p>
        <div class="keywords">
          <span class="keyword">QSP Modeling</span>
          <span class="keyword">Drug Synergy</span>
          <span class="keyword">MATLAB SimBiology</span>
          <span class="keyword">In Silico Experiments</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="area">
        <h3>Drug Combination Discovery</h3>
        <p>
          Developing computational pipelines to systematically measure and predict drug interactions at scale.
          Applied methods like DiaMOND (Diagonal Measurement Of N-way Drug interactions) to identify synergistic
          combinations against M. tuberculosis and M. abscessus, processing hundreds of thousands of drug screens.
        </p>
        <div class="keywords">
          <span class="keyword">High-Throughput Screening</span>
          <span class="keyword">Machine Learning</span>
          <span class="keyword">Network Analysis</span>
          <span class="keyword">Predictive Modeling</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="projects">
      <h2>Current & Recent Projects</h2>

      <div class="project-card">
        <h3>AP-1 Network Dynamics in Melanoma</h3>
        <p class="project-status">Ongoing | 2021 - Present</p>
        <p>
          Mechanistic modeling of AP-1 transcription factor dynamics to understand cellular plasticity
          in melanoma. Integrating Boolean modeling, partial correlation networks, and ODE frameworks
          with multiplexed single-cell imaging data.
        </p>
        <div class="project-links">
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1101/2025.11.06.686987" class="link">Preprint</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <h3>QSP Models for DNA Damage Response</h3>
        <p class="project-status">Completed | Summer 2025</p>
        <p>
          Developed novel Quantitative Systems Pharmacology models in MATLAB SimBiology to predict
          synergistic drug combinations targeting DNA damage response pathways. Conducted in silico
          experiments to inform optimal dosing strategies for drug-sensitive and resistant phenotypes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <h3>TB Drug Combination Landscapes</h3>
        <p class="project-status">Completed | 2018 - 2021</p>
        <p>
          Systematic measurement of drug combination landscapes using DiaMOND to predict in vivo tuberculosis
          treatment outcomes. Developed automated pipelines processing 300,000+ screens and machine learning
          models to prioritize combinations for animal testing.
        </p>
        <div class="project-links">
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.xcrm.2022.100737" class="link">Publication</a>
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cels.2021.08.004" class="link">Cell Systems Paper</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <h3>M. abscessus Drug Interactions</h3>
        <p class="project-status">Completed | 2020 - 2023</p>
        <p>
          Mapped the drug interaction landscape of Mycobacterium abscessus, identifying novel synergies
          and isolate-specific responses. Demonstrated how systematic drug interaction measurements can
          reveal pathogen-specific vulnerabilities.
        </p>
        <div class="project-links">
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1128/aac.00090-23" class="link">Publication</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .research-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: #00ff41;
    text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.5);
  }

  h1::before {
    content: '# ';
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem;
    color: #00ff41;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #00ff41;
  }

  h2::before {
    content: '## ';
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #c0c0c0;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .area {
    background-color: #0d0d0d;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    border-left: 4px solid #00ff41;
    border: 1px solid #00ff41;
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }

  .area:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.2);
  }

  .area h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #e0e0e0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .area h3::before {
    content: '>>> ';
    color: #00ff41;
  }

  .area p {
    color: #c0c0c0;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .keywords {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .keyword {
    background-color: transparent;
    color: #00ff41;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    border: 1px solid #00ff41;
  }

  .project-card {
    background-color: #0d0d0d;
    border: 1px solid #404040;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.1);
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }

  .project-card:hover {
    border-color: #00ff41;
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.2);
  }

  .project-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: #e0e0e0;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .project-status {
    color: #00ff41;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .project-status::before {
    content: '[';
  }

  .project-status::after {
    content: ']';
  }

  .project-card p {
    color: #c0c0c0;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .project-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .link {
    color: #00ff41;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #00ff41;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .link:hover {
    background-color: #00ff41;
    color: #0d0d0d;
    box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.5);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .area,
    .project-card {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
